The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | One-stop destination for plant lovers
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       One-stop destination for plant lovers
          A STAFF REPORTER                          House plants can liven up any home. A Telegraph picture                                  
	The House Plant Expo, being organised by the Agri-horticultural Society of India, will have a host of attractions for plant lovers, from demonstrations on how to decorate houses with plants to tips on using medicinal plants at home.         
	To be held from November 13 to 16 on the societys premises in Alipore, the expo is also the biggest competition of growing house plants. Its aim is to popularise plants in households to counter the disappearance of greens from the city.        
	The objective is to encourage people to put a plant in the house, especially as houses with gardens are becoming a thing of the past. Every house plant will contribute a tiny bit to the fight against global warming and pollution, said Nirupam Sen, the CEO of the society.        
	The expo will have all kinds of house plants and provide a common platform for growers, vendors and customers. Visitors can buy plants and take tips from experts and growers.        
	On November 14, the society will organise an inter-school debate on industrialisation at the cost of farmland is prejudicial to the interest of the country. We want to involve schoolchildren so that the seeds of interest can be sown early, said an organiser.        
	The society is organising the expo in collaboration with the state department of food processing industries and horticulture, National Horticultural Board and the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Authority.                                                                                                                                                                         
